summary:
The Security Council:

Reaffirms its determination to combat impunity for international crimes and ensure that all persons indicted by the ICTR and ICTY are brought to justice, recalling the mandate of the International Residual Mechanism for Criminal Tribunals (Mechanism) established by resolution 1966 (2010).

Recalling the Security Council Press Statement of 31 December 2017, and Articles 25 and 26 of the Statute of the Mechanism.

Decides to appoint Mr. Serge Brammertz as Prosecutor of the Mechanism with effect from 1 July 2018 until 30 June 2020.

Underlines that States should cooperate fully with the Mechanism.

Commends States that have accepted the relocation of acquitted or convicted persons and reiterates its call upon all States to cooperate with the Mechanism.

Urges all States, especially those where fugitives are suspected to be at large, to intensify cooperation with the Mechanism.

Emphasizes that the Mechanism is a small, temporary, and efficient structure with diminishing functions and size.

Welcomes the report submitted by the Mechanism and the report of the Office of Internal Oversight Services (OIOS).

Takes note of the Mechanism's work, including development of a legal and regulatory framework and procedures.

Notes the views and recommendations made by the Council's Informal Working Group on International Tribunals.

Requests the Mechanism to take into account those views, implement recommendations, and continue to enhance efficiency and effective management.
